The executive of the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), Oyo State council has engaged the services of external auditors, Update Consulting, for the forensic auditing of its Pen Group of Schools and Guest Houses. This was contained in a statement issued by the Secretary, Mr Sola Oladapo, and made available to newsmen on Tuesday in Ibadan. It said that the decision to engage the audit firm was reached, on Monday, at a meeting held with the management of the school and guest houses. The statement said that the Ibadan-based audit firm is expected to do a forensic audit of the school and guest houses from 2017 to 2019. Ex-servicemen, war veterans promise expertise assistance for… Sen Akanbi condoles Oyo people, Alaafin, govt over Akesan… UPDATE: One dead, three injured as fire razes Akesan market… Oyo NUJ assures members of quality welfare packages ALSO READ: NYSC denies involvement of corps member in Yenagoa police shooting It said that the audit firm would work with a newly constituted committee  for a period of one week starting from Wednesday, January 8. The new committee has Oladapo, the union Secretary as the Chairman, Mr Gboyega Ogunsina, an educationist, Alhaji Wasiu Asekun, the school’s PTA Chairman and Pastor Adeola Oduola, immediate Past Assistant Secretary of the union. Also on the committee are Mr Lekan Yusuf, the council’s Administrative Officer, Mrs Kemi Afolabi, the school’s Bursar and a school teacher as members. Other members are Mrs Jadesola Ajibola, the State NAWOJ Chairman, Mrs Femi Odekunle, Mr Jeremiah Oke, the union’s Treasurer, Mr Akeem Abas and Mrs Titi Adeyemi of the State Ministry. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE